title: Embossed Wool, early 18th century
medium:
Medium: wool
Technique: stamped (so-called moreen) plain cloth.
description: Louis XIV. Symmetrical design of big bouquets in lobed framing band decorated with various flowers and diapered areas. Various ground diapers suggesting lace patterns. Stamped and glazed on fine white wool ground.
